New lives, worlds, or universes are all at our fingertips. We can either make one, read one, or write about one. Which do you choose?
We all have one life to live, but thousands of lives to tell if we can just help them escape from our mind. Write everyday.
The absolute best way to help other people is to become your absolute best. Do something everyday to make that happen.
A good day is when you have a fun plan ahead. A GREAT day is when it all comes together. Wishing you all a GREAT DAY!
The anticipation for a new event is sometimes more emotionally intense than the event itself. Enjoy it all.
The Cary Wolfe novel is available here: http://t.co/gVTYefOY7a Working on the next in the series. Please check it out.
Sometimes it's just the throw away lines that mean a great deal to others. Have a nice day; You look great; Thank you; or just a big smile.
Have a GREAT DAY. And by GREAT, I mean whatever makes you HAPPY.  And by DAY, I mean your LIFE.
Every step we take leads us to something. It's up to us whether that is a positive, neutral, or negative step.
No matter how far you fall, there is ALWAYS a recovery plan just waiting to be implemented.
Grab onto your goals with both hands, and hold on tight. There's no other way to make sure it stays yours.
Style vs. Substance.  Does it really need to be VERSUS?
When you show a different face with different people, does anyone really recognize you?
Don't live your life like it's a dress rehearsal. Live it like every minute matters.
Sometimes mistakes happen for a reason. Before we go back to try and fix somethings we should really weigh the benefit of what is there.
